Here’s an ideal holiday date night in Denver. ❄️🩰

Head downtown to the Four Seasons and have dinner at Edge. Dress to impress. Valet is only $10 once validated by the restaurant. @fsdenver @edgesteakhouse 

I highly recommend the Maryland Crab Soup & then get a steak.

Following dinner, leave your car at the Four Seasons and walk over to the Denver Performing Arts Center - it’s only a 3 minute walk. There you can see the Denver Ballet perform the nutcracker at the Ellie Caulkins Opera House. @artscomplexdenver 

An usher will be able to help you find your seats. We were in the orchestra pit so we were able to see the musicians getting ready to go & then it was show time. The waltz of the snowflakes is always my favorite.

Following the show we walked back over to Edge & grabbed our car. Best night!

Wondering where to take your out of town friends when they’re visiting Denver? I got you.

First stop is Cholon for dinner - they have my death row meal. The french onion soup dumplings will be the best thing you’ve ever put in your mouth. Trust me. The French Onion Soup Dumplings are made with french onion soup & gruyere cheese. Also try General Cho’s dumplings & the vegetarian seasonal dumplings while you’re there. @cholon_denver 

Second stop is Union Station. Head upstairs to the second story mezzanine to Cooper Lounge for a night cap & dessert. Cooper Lounge is a chic cocktail space that offers views of downtown Denver as well as a panoramic view of Union Station’s Great Hall. Cooper Lounge is known for their craft cocktails in beautiful glassware. For my cocktail, I had A Wonderful Life made with Tito’s Vodka, New Deal Ginger, Pimento Dram, Cranberry, 5-Spice, Almond, Lemon & Club Soda. For dessert we had the Black and White Chocolate Mousse made with Velvet White And Dark Chocolate Mousse, Mascarpone Brownie, and Fresh Strawberry. We enjoyed our cocktails & dessert while taking in the vibes of the space. @thecooperlounge @denverunionstation 

Follow along for more recommendations!

My favorite restaurant in Cabo? Los Tres Gallos. Located in the heart Cabo, Los Tres Gallos is an experience for those in search of the real aromas and flavors of Mexican cuisine. @lostresgallos 

We arrived and were seated on the large terrace lit by fairy lights. Our server Jonathan was phenomenal and made sure we ordered the best cocktails and food offerings. There was a live mariachi band that played throughout dinner (I was obsessed with them, they were so good and they kept the vibes and energy of the entire restaurant so high). They played Danza Kuduro, All Shook Up & their favorite song for us.

What to order:
- Classic Margarita
- Bone Marrow
- Empanadas
- Tequila
- Lamb Shank
- Chile Relleno
- Carajillo
- Mexican Coffee (made table side)

Where to travel in the US that looks like Italy?

Villa Della Luna in Sonoma, California is just the spot 🌿🍷. We stayed here over the weekend to see our friends get engaged & it was pure magic. The villa is a private, gated estate on nearly 5 acres with sweeping views of the Sonoma hillsides and Bay Area. It’s an Inspirato luxury accommodation ideally located for a wine country vacation. @inspirato

#inspirato #travel #sonoma

Who is seeing Taylor Swift in Denver this weekend?! 

Fingers crossed she plays ‘Castles Crumbling’ on Friday with Haley Williams. @taylorswift 🏰🌿🧚🏻✨

Need a fun dinner idea for a couples trip? 👇🏼

Hire a private chef for a dinner party. We did this while in Sonoma and it was my favorite night - Chef Eric Lee & staff were wonderful. @cheflauraleeca 

We started out on the patio with pistachio goat cheese balls. The goat cheese balls were creamy & tangy, encased in pistachios & enveloped a piece of crisp green apple.

We took some pictures & then headed inside for dinner. The wine was flowing as we celebrated our sweet friends’ engagement. 

Chef Eric was cooking away and for our first course we had seared scallops. They were plated & served beautifully - buttery & delicious. 

More champagne was opened (naturally).

For our second course we had the choice of Seared Salmon with Japanese rice or Espresso Rubbed Akaushi Wagyu New York Strip with mashed potatoes & charred broccolini. I had the Salmon and it was tender and mild with a delicate taste of furikake butter. 

For dessert we had Chocolate Peanut Butter Crème Brûlée paired with a Peanut Butter Chocolate Chip Cookie. Holy dessert heaven. 

That’s a wrap - follow for more!

“Fever dream high in the quiet of the night, you know that I caught it” @taylorswift 💖💐🌸🎶 

Who else got to see The Eras Tour in Denver?!

#taylorswift #theerastour #denver

Say yes to pool days at The Rally Hotel. @rallyhotel 🧜🏼‍♀️🌞🌇🌊

During our stay at The Rally, we had access to their rooftop pool and the skybridge rooftop deck - we spent most of our weekend here. The Denver Skyline surrounded us while we swam in the plunge pool & soaked up the Colorado sun. An elite summer day on all accounts. 

Stay tuned for the full review on denvher.com and book your stay at The Rally Hotel.

Alright Denver, did you know you can make custom hats right here in Cherry Creek? 👇🏼🤠

This is none other than Hats by Parker Thomas. This was my first time making a hat like this and it was so much fun. If you need a hat for the National Western Stock Show, country concert, or just chic western city living, this is the spot. @hatsbyparkerthomas 

First we picked out the style and color. Each hat & design depends on each customer, but most hats can be done in around 20 minutes. We were in the shop for about an hour because we were having such a good time.

I can’t say enough good things about Parker, Taylor & Garrett - they all were wonderful and really helped steer us in the right direction on what colors would look best with our hair and what accessories would look best on the hat. Since I had never done this before, the help was much needed (and appreciated)!

I went with a brown feather band and light red cord to be wrapped around the band twice. Then Taylor tied the cord in the back to make a short tail. Our hats were sized & steamed to get the perfect look. The steam made the hats more pliable to make custom crowns and brim shapes. Once the hat was back to room temperature, the new shape was set.

Then it was time to brand! This was one of my favorite parts of the hat making experience - it added so much personal character to each hat. I had ‘DENV.HER.’ branded on the bottom of the rim and also did Parker Thomas’ logo. Then I had a rose branded on the top.

Talk about a great activity to do with a friend. You can even book Hats by Parker Thomas for private events! They have their own retail display, steamer, tables and racks so they can take this show on the road just about anywhere.

My final look was burgundy western chic - love her.

Check it out and follow for more!

#hatsbyparkerthomas #customhats #cowboyhat
